  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "Alphabet demonstrated strong revenue momentum in 2025, with Q4 revenue reaching $113.9 billion, representing 11.29% year-over-year growth. This acceleration followed sequential quarterly growth rates of 6.86% in Q2 and 6.14% in Q3, indicating improving top-line trajectory throughout the year. Profitability metrics remained robust in Q4, with gross margin at 59.82%, operating margin at 31.61%, and net margin at 30.25%. These margin levels reflect the company's ability to scale operations efficiently while maintaining pricing power across its core advertising and cloud services businesses.",
